    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import sympy as sp\n",
    "\n",
    "x = sp.symbols('x')\n",
    "\n",
    "#Formula\n",
    "def laguerre_poly(n):\n",
    "    term = (x**n) * sp.exp(-x)\n",
    "    poly = (sp.exp(x) / sp.factorial(n)) * sp.diff(term, x, n)\n",
    "    return sp.simplify(poly)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Raices de 1 a 5\n",
    "for i in range(1, 6):\n",
    "    L_i = laguerre_poly(i)\n",
    "    print(f'Polinomio de Laguerre L_{i}(x): {L_i}')\n",
    "    roots = sp.solve(L_i, x)\n",
    "    print(f'Raíces de L_{i}(x): {roots}')\n",
    "    print('--------------------------------')\n",
    "\n",
    "#Ejemplo con valores numericos\n",
    "x_vals = np.linspace(0, 100) \n",
    "L_5 = laguerre_poly(5) #Polinomio de ejemplo\n",
    "f_lambdified = sp.lambdify(x, L_5, \"numpy\")  \n",
    "poly_vals = f_lambdified(x_vals) \n",
    "\n",
    "print(poly_vals)\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [
    {

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "T = np.array([-3, 2])\n",
    "R = np.array([2, -2])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Índices de refracción\n",
    "n0 = 1\n",
    "n1 = 1.33  \n",
    "\n",
    "# Función\n",
    "def camino_optico(x):\n",
    "    d0 = np.sqrt((x - T[0])**2 + T[1]**2)\n",
    "    d1 = np.sqrt((x - R[0])**2 + R[1]**2)\n",
    "    return n0 * d0 + n1 * d1\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "x_values = np.linspace(-5, 5, 500)\n",
    "ct_values = camino_optico(x_values)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Graficar la función camino óptico\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(x_values, ct_values, label='Camino óptico ct(x)', color=\"black\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Distancia (x)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Tiempo de viaje ct(x)')\n",
    "plt.title('Camino óptico del pulso de luz')\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=0, color='grey', linestyle='--', label='Superficie del agua (y=0)')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "# Primera derivada usando diferencias finitas centrales\n",
    "def primera_derivada(f, x, h):\n",
    "    return (f(x + h) - f(x - h)) / (2 * h)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Segunda derivada usando diferencias finitas centrales\n",
    "def segunda_derivada(f, x, h):\n",
    "    return (f(x + h) - 2 * f(x) + f(x - h)) / (h**2)\n",
    "# Newton_raphoson para minimizar\n",
    "def newton_raphson(f, x0, h, epsilon):\n",
    "    x = x0\n",
    "    while True:\n",
    "        f_prime = primera_derivada(f, x, h)\n",
    "        f_double_prime = segunda_derivada(f, x, h)\n",
    "        x_new = x - f_prime / f_double_prime\n",
    "        # Condición de convergencia\n",
    "        if abs(x_new - x) < epsilon:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        x = x_new\n",
    "    return x\n",
    "#Estimación inicial para Newton_Raphson \n",
    "x0 = 0.0\n",
    "#Valor de h\n",
    "h= 1 * 10**(-5)\n",
    "#Valor de Epsilon\n",
    "epsilon = 1 * 10**(-9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encontrar el mínimo usando Newton-Raphson\n",
    "x_min = newton_raphson(camino_optico, x0, h, epsilon)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calcular el tiempo mínimo de viaje\n",
    "t_min = camino_optico(x_min)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"El  X_mínimo se alcanza en x = {x_min:.10f} con un distancia de ct(x) = {t_min:.10f}\")"
   ]

    "#b.\n",
    "def lagrange(x):\n",
    "  y=np.sin(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "  vander=np.vander(x)\n",
    "  inver=np.linalg.inv(vander)\n",
    "  coef=np.dot(inver,y)\n",
    "  polinomio=np.poly1d(coef)\n",
    "  return polinomio"
   ]
